Section 1:
Act 640 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: H3/31/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1751
4
5 By: Representative Underwood
6 By: Senator J. Bryant
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING PUBLIC ASSISTANCE;
10 TO REQUIRE AN APPLICANT FOR TEMPORARY ASSISTANCE FOR
11 NEEDY FAMILIES PROGRAM BENEFITS TO ENGAGE IN JOB
12 SEARCH ACTIVITIES WHILE THE APPLICATION IS BEING
13 PROCESSED; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
14
15
Subtitle
16
17 TO REQUIRE AN APPLICANT FOR TEMPORARY
18 ASSISTANCE FOR NEEDY FAMILIES PROGRAM
19 BENEFITS TO ENGAGE IN JOB SEARCH
20 ACTIVITIES WHILE THE APPLICATION IS
21 BEING PROCESSED.
22
23 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
24
25 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 20-76-439(f), concerning authorization for
26 the Department of Human Services to promulgate rules related to job search
27 activities during the transitional employment assistance application process,
28 is amended to read as follows:
29 (f) The department may develop and promulgate rules requiring shall
30 require program applicants who have been determined to be job-ready to engage
31 in job search activities while the application is being processed.
32
33 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code ยง 20-76-444, concerning the Arkansas Work
34 Pays Program, is amended to add an additional subsection to read as follows:
35 (i) The department shall require Arkansas Work Pays Program applicants
36 who have been determined to be job-ready to engage in job search activities
*CRH144*
03-31-2025 13:21:28 CRH144
As Engrossed: H3/31/25 HB1751
1 while the Arkansas Work Pays Program application is being processed.
2
3 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code Title 20, Chapter 76, Subchapter 4, is
4 amended to add an additional section to read as follows:
5 20-76-447. Recipients of Temporary Assistance for Needy Families
6 benefits.
7 The Department of Human Services shall require an applicant for
8 Temporary Assistance for Needy Families benefits who has been determined to
9 be job-ready to engage in job search activities while his or her application
10 for benefits is being processed.
11
12 /s/Underwood
